    <statement><p>Find the prime factorization of <m>35</m>.</p>
<p><m>35={}</m><fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>5\cdot 7</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>After checking to see if small prime numbers divide <m>35</m>, we find that <m>5</m> is one divisor. So <m>35=5\cdot7</m>.</p>
<p>Since both <m>5</m> and <m>7</m> are prime, the prime factorization of <m>35</m> is <m>5\cdot7</m>.</p>
</solution>
